<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-11-27T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-11-27T07:00:00-05:00" n="546" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d546">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2932: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-27T20:00:00+08:00">November 27 [<hi rend="italic">28?</hi>], 1931—8 p.m.</date><lb/>[Received November
                                28—7:58 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>1019. Following from American Consul General at Mukden: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“November 27, 1 p.m. Official spokesman gave out following
                                    statement from Japanese headquarters but stated that it was to
                                    be taken as unofficial: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>‘In view of the fact that the present situation has
                                            become quieter, headquarters has decided to withdraw all
                                            troops to the east of the Liao River and establish them
                                            at points within the South Manchuria Railway zone. The
                                            number of troops outside the zone will be reduced to a
                                            minimum.’”</p>
                                    </quote></p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer>For the Minister:<lb/><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>